<h2 style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Link Cube</h2>

<div style="line-height:2">
<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">The Link Cube is also known as the "Base 10 Blocks". The Link Cube will help children to learn about number sense, place value, counting addition, subtraction, fraction, and decimal. It allows the children to visualize the value of the number and how numbers are formed.</p>

<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Drag the link cubes<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/icon_linkcube_ten.png" style="vertical-align:middle">in the blank area. The three boxes at the bottom will represent the place value of the numbers, ones, tens and hundreds. The number will appear when the link cubes are dragged according to their place value. To make the number appear or disappear, click the<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_visibility.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle">button. Click and drag the blank area to the left to get more space to place the link cubes.</p>

<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Use the<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_rotate_frame.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle">button to change the orientation of the 10 link cubes from vertical to horizontal or vice versa. To change the colours of any link cubes, select them and click on the<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/icon_linkcube_colours.png" style="vertical-align:middle">button. To remove all the link cubes in the blank area, click the<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_trash.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle">button.</p>

<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">The<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/icon_linkcube_ten.png" style="vertical-align:middle">and<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/icon_linkcube_hundred.png" style="vertical-align:middle">link cubes can be separated. To separate the link cubes into 1 or 10, double-click on the 10 or 100 link cubes. The link cubes cannot be combined once they are separated. To write numbers or cross out the link cubes, use the<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_pencil.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle">button. Double-click on the button to change the colours of the pencil. Use the<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_eraser.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle">or<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_clear.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle">button to remove all the scribbles with the pencil tool. To start counting a new set of link cubes, click the<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_reset.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle">button.</p>
</div>